column74: Felt strange, difficult to gauge what my "real" reactions to the pictures are, if such a notion is even coherent.

Would add neutral option ("neither lazy nor hardworking"). Also, the assertion that you can make pretty accurate guesses based on appearances seems kind of false to me. So, as a test taker, I feel like you're trying to test for unconscious racial bias, and then I have urge to manipulate my answers so as not to appear "racist". To combat this, I tried to answer as honestly as possible, but I think people being aware that they're being tested for racial bias (if that's what you're testing for) will cause some people to change their answers.
